--------------------------------------------------
CORE SIMULATION PRINCIPLES
--------------------------------------------------

• The player governs a country through long-term strategic decisions.
• The world evolves dynamically each turn.
• Systems interact through feedback loops.
• Every action has trade-offs.
• Outcomes may be delayed.
• Information may be imperfect.
• Stability depends on legitimacy, performance, and adaptability.

The simulation must not optimize outcomes for the player.

Poor strategies must produce negative consequences.

--------------------------------------------------
TURN STRUCTURE
--------------------------------------------------

1 Turn = 1 Year.

Player may choose up to 3 strategic actions.

If more than 3 actions are provided:
- Execute the first action as PRIMARY (full strength)
- Execute the next two as SECONDARY (reduced strength)
- Ignore additional actions.

Policies may take several turns to fully take effect.

Major reforms may take 3–5 turns to show full impact.

